    {# ── CSAT Paper 2 ── #}
    <h2 class="section-heading">CSAT — Paper 2 (Qualifying)</h2>

    <div class="info-card" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-6);">
      <div class="info-card__grid">
        <div class="info-card__item">
          <span class="info-card__num">80</span>
          <span class="info-card__label">Questions</span>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card__item">
          <span class="info-card__num">200</span>
          <span class="info-card__label">Marks</span>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card__item">
          <span class="info-card__num">2 hrs</span>
          <span class="info-card__label">Duration</span>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card__item">
          <span class="info-card__num">33%</span>
          <span class="info-card__label">Qualifying (66/200)</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="info-card__note">CSAT is qualifying only — marks are NOT added to merit. But failing it (below 33%) means your GS Paper 1 score doesn't count at all.</p>
    </div>

    <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap:var(--space-5); margin-bottom:var(--space-8);">
      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Comprehension</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">Largest section. Read the passage carefully — answers are always within the passage. Don't use outside knowledge. Practice reading speed and accuracy.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Logical Reasoning</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">Syllogisms, sequences, Venn diagrams, blood relations, direction sense. These are scoring — practice patterns and you'll get them right every time.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Basic Numeracy</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">Class 10 level math — percentages, ratios, averages, profit/loss, time-speed-distance. No calculators allowed. Practice mental math shortcuts.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Data Interpretation</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">Bar charts, pie charts, tables. Read data carefully, calculate quickly. Approximation is key — exact calculation wastes time.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Decision Making</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">Situational questions testing administrative aptitude. Choose the most balanced, ethical, and practical option. Avoid extreme positions.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">English Comprehension</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">English language questions at 10th class level. For non-English medium candidates — practice reading English passages daily. Marks here are easy to secure.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    {# ── Strategy Section ── #}
    <h2 class="section-heading">Prelims Strategy</h2>

    <div class="strategy-grid" style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr)); gap:var(--space-5); margin-bottom:var(--space-8);">

      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Elimination Technique</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">With -0.66 negative marking, attempt only when you can eliminate at least 2 options. Random guessing costs marks. Educated guessing after eliminating 2 options is statistically safe.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Target Score</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">Aim for 90+ correct with under 15 wrong. That gives ~110/200 net — comfortably above most cutoffs. Track your accuracy subject-wise to find weak areas.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Time Management</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">~1.2 minutes per question. Don't spend more than 2 minutes on any single question. Flag difficult ones and return to them after completing the easy ones.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Current Affairs Weight</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">30-40% questions are current affairs based. Read newspapers daily and maintain monthly compilations. Even static topics are often framed through recent events.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">CSAT — Don't Neglect</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">Paper 2 (CSAT) is qualifying at 33%, but candidates do fail it. Practice comprehension passages and basic math. 80 questions, 200 marks, -0.83 per wrong answer.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="strategy-card">
        <h4 class="strategy-card__title">Revision Cycle</h4>
        <p class="strategy-card__text">Read once, revise thrice. Use BharatNotes Vocab Builder and Key Terms to build exam-ready vocabulary. Revision in the last 2 months matters more than new topics.</p>
      </div>

    </div>

